<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-10-10T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-10-10T19:00:00-05:00" n="804" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d804">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">795A.00/11–1050: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                                <gloss type="to">United States Mission</gloss> at the United
                            Nations</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-10-10T19:00:00-05:00">November 10,
                                1950—7 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>495. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> thinks it wld be useful if when
                        reps of <gloss target="#t_IC3">IC</gloss> have established themselves and
                        are available to lend assistance on questions relating to NK frontier in
                        accordance with <gloss target="#t_IC3">IC</gloss> res of Nov 6[<hi rend="italic">7</hi>],<note n="1" xml:id="d804fn1">See telegram 303,
                            November 9, noon, to Seoul, <ref target="#pg_1115">p. 1115</ref>.</note>
                        they shld report this fact to SYG. SYG in turn might then arrange to make
                        authorities in Peiping aware of availability of <gloss target="#t_IC3">IC</gloss>’s reps.</p>
                    <p>Suggest you talk to SYG and perhaps Romulo along these lines.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>